               <msContents>
                  <summary>ʾAlfīyah is one of the most reliable grammatical works in the Arabic literature. It is a versified work including 1,000 couplets composed in Rajaz metric. ʾAlfīyah is compiled in 71 chapters. Numerous commentaries have been written on this work so far, of which Suyūṭ‭ī's commentary is the most popular in the Iranian religious schools.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="WadhMinasian_418-item1" n="1">
                     <locus from="1a" to="104a">ff. 1b-129b</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                     <note type="content-genre">Arabic language--Syntax</note>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_2268">ʾAlfīyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_2268">الفیه</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="work_2268">Arjūzah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" type="alt" key="work_2268">ارجوزه</title>
                     <author key="person_12537163" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/12537163">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">‎Ibn Mālik, Muḥammad ibn ʻAbd Allāh, -1274‏</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar" type="standard">ابن مالک، محمد بن عبدالله، -۱۲۷۴</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Ibn Mālik, Muḥammad ibn ʻAbd Allāh bin Mālik al-Andulusī, 600-12 Shaʿbān 672/1204-1274</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar" type="alt">ابن مالک، محمد بن عبدالله بن مالک الاندلسی، ۶۰۰-۱۲ شعبان ۶۷۲ق/۱۲۰۴-۱۲۷۴م</persName>
                     </author>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar">قال محمد هو ابن مالک / احمد ربی الله خیر مالک…</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar">… و آله الغز الکرام البرره / و صحبه المنتخبین الخیره.</explicit>
                     <colophon xml:lang="ar">تم الکتاب… فی یوم خمیس و فی عشر اول شهر جمادی الاخر… سنه ۱۲۴۱ فی ید…</colophon>
